eedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ysi1665702936257.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ysi1665702936257.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ysi1665702936257.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ysi1665702936257\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      DB2 Error Messages\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__dberror_messages_150931\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When an error has occurred, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$dberror</span> will be set to the error code DB2 has returned for that particular error.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__p_d49691e1_d49692e1_d49693e1\">The DB2-generated error text will be available in the message frame, or in the application’s log file when <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PUTMESS_LOG_FILE</span> is used in the assignment file. You can look up the error code in the documentation of DB2. The errors returned by DB2 (via <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$dberror</span>) are shown in the table:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">$dberror driver error messages</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Error</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Message</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-24</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The connector can fetch by primary key only.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-25</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No more cursors could be allocated.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-26</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No more statements could be allocated.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-27</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Connector deleted/updated more or less than 1 row.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-28</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">An illegal request was received by the connector.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-29</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Already logged on to a database.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-30</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The connector does not support this version of DB2.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-31</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The connector does not recognize this DBMS.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-32</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Could not obtain sufficient dynamic memory.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-33</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The result row bigger than uiobuf.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-34</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">General logic error in connector.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-35</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Error in USYS$DB2_PARAMS string.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-36</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Requested action results in empty fieldlist.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">-37</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ysi1665702936257__table_d4688e1_d4689e1_d4690e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Cannot execute next step. Cursor has been released.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__topic_d32647e1_d32648e1_d32649e1_d32650e1_d32651e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d742348e311\">\n                        \n iSeries\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ysi1665702936257__p_d49697e1_d49698e1_d49699e1\">On iSeries, you also have the possibility to use the CL command <code class=\"ph codeph\">DSPMSGD</code> to look up the error in the QSQLMSG message file. The message identifier to look up is SQL<var class=\"keyword varname\">xxxx</var>, where <var class=\"keyword varname\">xxxx</var> is the four-digit error number. For example, if the error code is <code class=\"ph codeph\">-913</code>, the identifier is <code class=\"ph codeph\">SQL0913</code>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zea1665702607771.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$PUTMESS_LOG_FILE</a><p>Copy the message frame contents to one or more files.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hms1665702684501.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$dberror</a><p>Return the error code reported by the DBMS.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534240\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534240\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DB2 Error Messages Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DB2 Error Messages When an error has occurred, $dberror will be set to the error code DB2 has returned for that particular error. The DB2-generated error text will be available in the message frame, or in the application’s log file when $PUTMESS_LOG_FILE is used in the assignment file. You can look up the error code in the documentation of DB2. The errors returned by DB2 (via $dberror ) are shown in the table: Table 1. $dberror driver error messages Error Message -24 The connector can fetch by primary key only. -25 No more cursors could be allocated. -26 No more statements could be allocated. -27 Connector deleted/updated more or less than 1 row. -28 An illegal request was received by the connector. -29 Already logged on to a database. -30 The connector does not support this version of DB2. -31 The connector does not recognize this DBMS. -32 Could not obtain sufficient dynamic memory. -33 The result row bigger than uiobuf. -34 General logic error in connector. -35 Error in USYS$DB2_PARAMS string. -36 Requested action results in empty fieldlist. -37 Cannot execute next step. Cursor has been released. iSeries On iSeries, you also have the possibility to use the CL command DSPMSGD to look up the error in the QSQLMSG message file. The message identifier to look up is SQL xxxx , where xxxx is the four-digit error number. For example, if the error code is -913 , the identifier is SQL0913 . Related Links $PUTMESS_LOG_FILE Copy the message frame contents to one or more files. $dberror Return the error code reported by the DBMS. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}